description: Brent Sprecher came out of the same tiny Wisconsin town that spawned comic book professionals Brandon Peterson (Uncanny X-Men) and Scott Kolins (The Flash). He got his start penciling a variety of projects for Caliber Comics before moving into the video game industry. He returned to comics in 2007, providing cover artwork and pin-ups for Bluewater Comics before writing a string of bio-comics for Bluewater, including books on Ted Kennedy and Angelina Jolie. Sprecher designed numerous characters and provided cover artwork for the superhero role-playing game Capes, Cowls & Villains Foul from Spectrum Games, as well as for its follow-up CCVF: Gallery of Evil. He co-created and wrote the four-issue all-ages adventure comic book Spaced Out, which debuted in 2014, and is the cover artist for the Lightweightnovel series from Metahuman Press. Sprecher is currently developing creator-owned properties for both the comic book medium and television.
name: Brent Sprecher
